# DCP Frontend UI System

Apply this for every frontend change.

## Stack
- Next.js App Router + React + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS with HSL CSS variable tokens
- Radix primitives + CVA variants for reusable components
- `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` via a shared `cn()` helper
- `tailwindcss-animate` for stateful transitions
- Framer Motion only for subtle custom motion
- `lucide-react` icons (`h-4 w-4` default)
- Geist Sans typography
- Forms use React Hook Form + Zod schemas

## Color Tokens
Use CSS variables and map through Tailwind token names. Keep monochrome palette:
- `--background` `0 0% 100%` (dark: `0 0% 3.9%`)
- `--foreground` `0 0% 3.9%` (dark: `0 0% 98%`)
- `--primary` `0 0% 9%` (dark: `0 0% 98%`)
- `--secondary` `0 0% 96.1%` (dark: `0 0% 14.9%`)
- `--muted` `0 0% 96.1%` (dark: `0 0% 14.9%`)
- `--accent` `0 0% 96.1%` (dark: `0 0% 14.9%`)
- `--destructive` `0 84.2% 60.2%` (dark: `0 62.8% 30.6%`)
- `--border` `0 0% 89.8%` (dark: `0 0% 14.9%`)
- `--ring` `0 0% 3.9%` (dark: `0 0% 83.1%`)

Chart tokens:
- `--chart-1: 12 76% 61%`
- `--chart-2: 173 58% 39%`
- `--chart-3: 197 37% 24%`
- `--chart-4: 43 74% 66%`
- `--chart-5: 27 87% 67%`

## Shape / Depth / Layout
- `--radius: 0.5rem` (lg=8px, md=6px, sm=4px)
- Cards `rounded-lg border bg-card shadow-sm`
- Buttons `rounded-md`
- Badges `rounded-full`
- Minimal depth: cards `shadow-sm`, popovers `shadow-md`, modals `shadow-lg`
- Container: `max-w-[1920px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6`
- Mobile-first: stacked on mobile, multi-column on `md+`

## Interaction Patterns
- Buttons use CVA variants: `default | destructive | outline | secondary | ghost | link`
- Button heights: default `h-10`, small `h-9`, large `h-11`
- Inputs: `h-10 rounded-md border border-input bg-background px-3 py-2 text-sm`
- Focus style: `focus-visible:ring-2 ring-ring ring-offset-2 ring-offset-background`
- Use `sr-only` text where needed
- Use semantic sections, headings, labels, and landmarks

## Motion
- Keep motion subtle (`~200ms`)
- Prefer `transition-colors` / `transition-opacity`
- Radix state classes: `data-[state=open]:animate-in` and `data-[state=closed]:animate-out`
- Small offsets (`zoom-in-95`, `slide-in-from-*-2`)

## Visual Direction
Minimal, clean, monochrome. Emphasize hierarchy with spacing and typography, not decorative effects.
Avoid heavy gradients, glow, and glassmorphism.
